item.description:
In Ubuntu, PyCharm conflicts with the gnome desktop shortcuts, which makes key-bindings Ctrl+Alt+Left and Ctrl+Alt+Right not work.
Use below commands to remove the shortcuts from gnome desktop.
1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8  # List the current shortcuts. liangr@ubuntu-dev:~$ gsettings list-recursively org.gnome.desktop.wm.keybindings | grep Left org.gnome.desktop.wm.keybindings move-to-monitor-left [&#39;&lt;Super&gt;&lt;Shift&gt;Left&#39;] org.gnome.desktop.wm.keybindings move-to-workspace-left [&#39;&lt;Control&gt;&lt;Shift&gt;&lt;Alt&gt;Left&#39;] org.gnome.desktop.wm.keybindings switch-to-workspace-left [&#39;&lt;Control&gt;&lt;Alt&gt;Left&#39;] liangr@ubuntu-dev:~$ gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.wm.keybindings switch-to-workspace-left &#34;[]&#34; liangr@ubuntu-dev:~$ gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.wm.keybindings switch-to-workspace-right &#34;[]&#34;
